{
  "stem": "8784.5",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I-- in fact, I do.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One of the memorable things that happened during that six-month stay in Brunnlitz is that at one point in time-- and I, again, cannot place it exactly in the timing-- but it was sometime in 1945-- that into that small camp of Brunnlitz, Amon Goeth arrived, the same killer that we left over in Krakow-Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we thought that he disappeared and is gone from our life.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Lo and behold, he appeared there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I saw him walking through the factory building, but it was not the same Amon Goeth.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He must have been-- after he lost a great amount of weight, the uniform hung on him.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It did not fit him anymore.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was stripped of his ranks.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was no longer any spic and span in him.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And as we know now, there is a good chance that Amon Goeth came out of jail, arriving to Schindler if Schindler could help him out for the rest of the war.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But I remember him a totally different man-- thin, losing a lot of weight, uniform hanging on him, and no decorations anymore than what-- what I remembered seeing him in Krakow-Plaszow.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in Krakow-Plaszow, I did have occasions to see him close up as he walked by on the street.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "On occasion, I saw him walking with Mietek Pemper discussing-- Mietek Pemper was a sort of a Jewish secretary to Amon Goeth.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He was an intellectual and educated person, evidently.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And Amon Goeth took a liking to him, and he had him be his secretary.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I saw him also close up on occasions when lynchings were going on all around the appellplatz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So I knew Amon Goeth by sight at that time.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So when he arrived in Brunnlitz, it was a total shock.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
